<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920323-0033</DOCNO><DOCID>920323-0033.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Finmeccanica S.p.A.:   Capital Increase Stepped Up   In Proposal to Go Public</HL><DATE>03/23/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6B</SO><CO>   I.IRI I.MEC</CO><MS>CONGLOMERATES (CGL)FINANCIAL (FIN)INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>CONGLOMERATES (CGL)DIVERSIFIED FINANCIAL SERVICES (FIS)DIVERSIFIED INDUSTRIAL (IDD)REAL ESTATE INVESTMENTS (REA)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>RESTRUCTURINGS, RECAPITALIZATION (RCN)ACQUISITIONS, MERGERS, TAKEOVERS (TNM)</NS><RE>EUROPE (EU)ITALY (ITA)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   Finmeccanica S.p.A. of Italy will launch an additional 700billion-lire ($556.8 million) capital increase for Italianand foreign institutional investors under its plan to gopublic, bringing the total amount of fresh funds coming fromthe group's restructuring to 2.6 trillion lire, the stateholding company that owns it said.   As previously reported, Istituto per la RicostruzioneIndustriale, the holding company, said Finmeccanica, itsengineering unit, plans to obtain a Milan Stock Exchangelisting by merging with Finmeccanica's publicly tradedfinancial services and real-estate unit, Societa Immobiliaree Finanziaria.</LP><TEXT>   The Finmeccanica group includes a railroad equipmentmaker, an aerospace and defense unit, and an automationcontrols subsidiary. It also holds interests in energygeneration, bioengineering and microprocessors. Eventually asmuch as 40% of Finmeccanica's share capital is expected to betraded.   Sources familiar with the restructuring said it probablywill happen in the fall.</TEXT></DOC>